# Solana Tools Brand + Color Palette

## Brand Direction

- This site must feel **serious, modern, technical, and trustworthy** (financial/crypto tooling), not like a “crypto casino”.
- **Avoid spraying Solana neon green** across the UI. Use Solana/Web3 cues subtly via **cyan** accents instead.
- Primary identity is **Blue/Cyan**. Purple is a **secondary flavor** for highlights only.
- Base neutrals should remain **Slate-like** for readability in long SEO pages and forms.

## Color System (CSS Variables Reference)

Use these tokens as the source-of-truth palette for light/dark mode. Prefer mapping Tailwind usage to these roles (background, foreground, card, border, primary, etc.).

### Light mode

```css
:root {
  --background: #F8FAFC;
  --foreground: #0F172A;

  --card: #FFFFFF;
  --card-foreground: #0F172A;

  --primary: #2563EB;
  --primary-hover: #1D4ED8;
  --primary-foreground: #FFFFFF;

  --secondary: #7C3AED;
  --secondary-hover: #6D28D9;

  --accent: #06B6D4;
  --accent-soft: #E0F7FA;

  --muted: #F1F5F9;
  --muted-foreground: #64748B;

  --border: #E2E8F0;
  --input: #CBD5E1;

  --success: #16A34A;
  --warning: #F59E0B;
  --danger: #DC2626;

  --sidebar: #FFFFFF;
  --sidebar-foreground: #334155;
  --sidebar-active: #EFF6FF;
  --sidebar-active-foreground: #1D4ED8;
}
```

### Dark mode

```css
.dark {
  --background: #020617;
  --foreground: #E5E7EB;

  --card: #0F172A;
  --card-foreground: #F8FAFC;

  --primary: #38BDF8;
  --primary-hover: #0EA5E9;
  --primary-foreground: #020617;

  --secondary: #A78BFA;
  --secondary-hover: #8B5CF6;

  --accent: #22D3EE;
  --accent-soft: rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.12);

  --muted: #111827;
  --muted-foreground: #94A3B8;

  --border: #1E293B;
  --input: #334155;

  --success: #22C55E;
  --warning: #FBBF24;
  --danger: #F87171;

  --sidebar: #020617;
  --sidebar-foreground: #CBD5E1;
  --sidebar-active: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.12);
  --sidebar-active-foreground: #7DD3FC;
}
```

## UI Usage Guidance (Tailwind-first)

### Header

- Light: `bg-white border-b border-slate-200`
- Dark: `dark:bg-slate-950 dark:border-slate-800`
- Main CTA:
  - `bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700`
  - `dark:bg-sky-400 dark:text-slate-950 dark:hover:bg-sky-300`

### Sidebar

- Active item: `bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 dark:bg-sky-400/10 dark:text-sky-300`
- Normal item: `text-slate-600 hover:bg-slate-100 hover:text-slate-950 dark:text-slate-300 dark:hover:bg-slate-900 dark:hover:text-white`
- Icons: `text-slate-400 group-hover:text-blue-600 dark:text-slate-500 dark:group-hover:text-sky-300`

### Cards / Tool Boxes

- Light: `bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm`
- Dark: `dark:bg-slate-900 dark:border-slate-800`
- Hover (subtle, no animation): `hover:border-blue-300 dark:hover:border-sky-700`

### Forms

- Input: `bg-white border-slate-300 text-slate-900 dark:bg-slate-950 dark:border-slate-700 dark:text-slate-100`
- Focus: `focus:border-blue-500 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500/20 dark:focus:border-sky-400 dark:focus:ring-sky-400/20`
- Error: `border-red-500 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400`
- Warning box: `bg-amber-50 border-amber-200 text-amber-900 dark:bg-amber-950/30 dark:border-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200`

## SEO Pages (important)

- Keep readable neutral surfaces; avoid loud gradients, neon blocks, or purple-overuse.
- Use cyan/purple only as **small accents** (badges, highlights, links, subtle hero background).

## Allowed “Hero Gradient” (subtle, CSS-only)

Use only on key landing areas; keep it subtle and static (no animation).

Light:

```css
bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top_right,rgba(56,189,248,0.18),transparent_35%),radial-gradient(circle_at_top_left,rgba(124,58,237,0.14),transparent_30%)]
```

Dark:

```css
dark:bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top_right,rgba(56,189,248,0.16),transparent_35%),radial-gradient(circle_at_top_left,rgba(167,139,250,0.12),transparent_30%)]
```

## Hard “Don’ts”

- Do not use Solana neon green as the site’s dominant UI color.
- Do not add animation libraries or animated gradients.
- Do not make the UI “flashy”; it must read like a serious tool.
